/target
**/*.rs.bk

# Local sqlite DBs + dev-mode email fallback. The example app writes its DB
# under the workspace target/ dir; library tests may create them there too.
# The patterns below also catch any stray auth.db left in a crate cwd.
**/auth.db
**/auth.db-journal
**/auth.db-wal
**/auth.db-shm
**/emails/

# Docker runtime state from examples/*/docker-compose.yml: the bind-mounted
# ./data dir holds the SQLite DB (auth.db / auth-leptos.db) and the .eml
# mailer output. Host-owned and per-environment — never committed.
examples/*/data/

# Local secrets. SMTP creds, OAuth client secrets, the bootstrap-admin email,
# anything else that lives in a per-environment dotenv file. `.env.example`
# is unignored so a tracked template (placeholder values, no secrets) is
# allowed to land in the repo.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Personal scratch notes
TODO.md
TODO*.md

# Local security-testing scratch: the THC-Hydra brute-force script, the
# hardening-verification harness, and their generated wordlist. Created
# ad-hoc to exercise an example's auth against credential and authz
# attacks; not part of the shipped example. (The access-control probe is
# tracked, not ignored — CI runs it as a regression gate.)
examples/*/hydra-login-test.sh
examples/*/harden-verify.sh
examples/*/ffuf-discover.sh
examples/*/hydra.restore
examples/*/passwords.txt

# Editor / OS junk
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
